Ad Text:
New Project
12 months (with potential extension)
Immediate interview and start



We are seeking a Senior Project Manager to lead the end-to-end program focused on transforming a legacy Oracle Data Warehouse and OBIEE reporting environment to align with new data structures introduced by a greenfield SAP S/4HANA implementation. Essential Skills


Proven experience delivering BI/Data Warehouse migration or ERP data migration programs-ideally where Oracle to SAP alignment was central.
Strong familiarity with ETL, data modelling, data integration, and reporting lifecycle across analysis, build, test, and cutover.
Exceptional scope and change control discipline-able to create clarity, sequence work, and keep the right things in scope when time is tight.
Hands-on documentation capability-you write the docs that people actually use (scope, stakeholder decks, contracts/SoWs, functional specs).
Comfortable operating in complex, multi-party environments-experienced collaborating with product partners (e.g., Amplify) and internal teams.
Clear communicator-translates technical detail into business speak; aligns execs and practitioners to a single plan.

Position overview

Permanent, Full-Time opportunity

$166,650 per annum inclusive of 12% superannuation

About us
We're on a mission to create a brighter future, where you can be a change maker at the actual source. We're one of Australia's largest water utilities with over 30% of Victoria's population relying on us for their essential water and sanitation services.

Our award-winning culture fosters an inclusive, collaborative, and flexible environment that enables our people to thrive. Here, you'll be inspired and challenged to grow alongside us.

The role
We're looking for a Senior Data Analytics Specialist - Operations who brings advanced, hands-on experience with Power BI and deep expertise in Semantic Modelling, DAX, and modern data visualization frameworks.

In this pivotal role, you'll bridge analytics, reporting, and collaboration with both business and technical stakeholders, ensuring that insights are accurate, timely, and actionable. You will work closely with business stakeholders and data engineering teams to ensure reporting solutions are built on governed, high-quality, and scalable data pipelines.

As part of the Operations team, you'll take ownership of the ongoing health, reliability, and performance of our enterprise reporting environment. This includes monitoring and ensuring report and data pipeline refreshes, managing and prioritizing items in the EDA service queue, and efficiently troubleshooting or resolving incidents. You will also drive continuous improvement through enhancing and optimizing reports, improving data model performance, and supporting BAU activities such as dataset maintenance, access governance, and version control.

In addition to operational support, the role will involve new report and dashboard development as part of enhancement work, continuous improvement initiatives, or issue remediation. You'll be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining Power BI solutions that deliver trusted, high-quality insights aligned with business needs.

Experience with modern data platforms such as Azure Databricks is highly valued, enabling you to contribute to data transformations and the ongoing enhancement of our enterprise analytics ecosystem.

Your key responsibilities

Build and maintain robust enterprise semantic models that support advanced analytics, operational reporting, and self-service capabilities.
Translate complex business processes and requirements into functional specifications and scalable data models that align with enterprise architecture, governance, and performance frameworks.
Develop semantic models and measures optimized for performance, usability, and security - including the implementation of row-level security and other access controls.
Create impactful dashboards and data visualizations that deliver actionable insights and enable data-driven decision-making across business stakeholders.
Ensure all solutions adhere to data governance, information management, and IT security policies, with comprehensive documentation following approved project methodologies and templates.
Monitor and manage the performance, reliability, and refresh status of reports, datasets, and data pipelines to ensure seamless daily operations.
Oversee and prioritize items in the EDA service queue, addressing incidents, troubleshooting refresh or performance failures, and implementing effective resolutions.
Drive continuous improvement through enhancements to existing reports and data models, ensuring scalability, consistency, and alignment with evolving business needs.
Design, develop, and optimize modern data pipelines and transformations using Azure Databricks (PySpark) and related tools to ensure scalable, high-quality data delivery and integration.
Collaborate with business stakeholders and data engineering teams to maintain governed, high-performing, and future-ready analytics solutions across the enterprise environment.

What we're looking for

Extensive experience designing and developing enterprise-grade, self-service dashboards and reports using Power BI, with a focus on usability, performance, and data storytelling.
Expertise in Power BI semantic modelling, including DAX, Power Query, and advanced visualization frameworks such as the 3-30-300 rule to tailor insights for diverse audience needs.
Skilled in translating complex business requirements into compelling data visualisations, KPIs, and actionable insights, ensuring alignment with strategic objectives.
Proven track record in Power BI performance optimisation, leveraging tools such as Tabular Editor, DAX Studio, and ALM Toolkit for model tuning and deployment efficiency.
Experience in maintaining and optimising Power BI semantic models, datasets, and dataflows, with integration capabilities across Azure Databricks and other cloud data platforms.
Strong proficiency in SQL for data extraction, transformation, validation, and preparation for reporting use cases.
Adept at managing operational reporting environments, including monitoring data refreshes, ensuring report reliability, and maintaining data integrity.
Delivered effective training and enablement sessions to boost organisational BI tool adoption and self-service reporting capabilities.
Collaborative communicator, skilled at engaging business stakeholders and subject matter experts (SMEs) to define KPIs, gather requirements, and co-create valuable reporting solutions.
Holds a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Data Engineering, Information Systems, or a related technical field.

The Data & Analytics Technology team underpins these efforts by providing essential services to our primary stakeholder, the Data & Analytics Office.Â

The role

As a Data Modeller you will be responsible for translating complex business requirements into clear, scalable data models across conceptual, logical and physical layers. These models will underpin analytics, reporting and operational processes. Collaborating closely with data engineers, analysts and business stakeholders the Data Modeller will ensure that data assets are well-structured, standardised and fully aligned with established governance and quality frameworks.

Strong experience with relational and data warehouse design techniques and modelling methodologies (Kimball, Inmon, Data Vault 2.0, NoSQL).

Comprehensive knowledge of established data management principles, frameworks, and technologies.

ASIC's Data & Analytics Technology team is seeking an experienced and highly capable Data Modeller to join their high performing team.

Â 

Sydney or Melbourne locations
24-month fixed term position
Salary from $163,970 to $181,284 (depending on experience) + 15.4 % superannuation
Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, Sunday 18 January 2026Â 

Â 

The teamÂ 

ASIC's Digital, Data & Technology group delivers a broad suite of IT capabilities to support ASIC. We are currently driving major technology initiatives that will accelerate our transformation across key areas including virtualisation, data analytics, mobility, and cloud. The Data & Analytics Technology team underpins these efforts by providing essential services to our primary stakeholder, the Data & Analytics Office.Â 

Â 

The role

As a Data Modeller you will be responsible for translating complex business requirements into clear, scalable data models across conceptual, logical and physical layers. These models will underpin analytics, reporting and operational processes. Collaborating closely with data engineers, analysts and business stakeholders the Data Modeller will ensure that data assets are well-structured, standardised and fully aligned with established governance and quality frameworks.

Â 

More specifically, you will:Â 

Design and maintain conceptual, logical and physical data models to support development and enhancements across ASIC's data infrastructure, including but not limited to data lakes, application databases, and BI/analytics solutions.
Collaborate effectively with business stakeholders and application/solution teams to define requirements and document data transformations.
Conduct peer reviews of data models developed by team members and external suppliers to ensure quality and consistency.
Take on additional responsibilities and tasks as required, demonstrating flexibility and commitment to team objectives.
Work in a professional, positive and cooperative manner, modelling ASIC's core values of Accountability, Professionalism and Teamwork.

Â 

About you

The ideal candidate for this role is a data modelling professional who thrives on turning complex business challenges into elegant, scalable solutions. With deep expertise in data modelling tools and strong knowledge of relational and NoSQL technologies, you will bring both technical precision and strategic insight expertise. You will communicate with clarity, collaborate seamlessly across teams, while championing data governance and quality more broadly. Adaptable and values-driven, you will embody ASIC's principles of Accountability, Professionalism and Teamwork while delivering impactful outcomes.

Â 

In addition, you will have:

Proven ability to quickly interpret complex business requirements and translate them into logical and physical data models using industry-standard modelling tools.
Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, with the capability to convey technical concepts clearly to non-technical audiences.
Extensive hands-on experience with ERwin Data Modeller for designing and maintaining data models.
Strong experience with relational and data warehouse design techniques and modelling methodologies (Kimball, Inmon, Data Vault 2.0, NoSQL).
Familiarity with cloud data platforms and technologies (e.g. AWS, Databricks).
Comprehensive knowledge of established data management principles, frameworks, and technologies.

Â

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

ASIC is committed to a providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Indigenous Australians are encouraged to apply as well as applicants from all backgrounds and with different abilities.

Principal BI Solution Architect, Ongoing opportunity based in Sydney CBD + hybrid/flexible working options available

Ongoing, full-time opportunity
Clerk grade:11/12
Salary range: $149,739 - $173,174 p.a. plus superannuation and leave loading
Location: Sydney

Help solve the State's most challenging problems with data and analytics.
What drives State decisions around housing? What determines safety standards across our workplaces? And how does the State decide the best allocation of resources and funding?

The most challenging Government problems are solved using analytics. The best outcomes for NSW citizens are driven by reliable data and insights, developed by highly skilled and motivated analytics teams. This is your opportunity to join one of them.

If you're passionate about transforming data into actionable insights that shape policy, improve public services, and drive smarter decision-making, join the Department of Customer Service as a Principal BI Solution Architect - where your expertise will directly impact critical government initiatives.

You'll be joining a motivated and high-performing analytics team who:

Have a defined remit to develop and deliver high-value analytics use cases for DCS and its leaders
Are trusted advisors to the executive leadership team, with proven strategic and analytical expertise and a track record of delivering impactful budget, people and regulatory outcomes for the Department
Have an established reputation, strong executive presence and play a key role in influencing business decisions and direction through analytics
Own, maintain and develop several critical reporting solutions for the Department and its external partner agencies
Strive to create value and drive business outcomes through every data point, insight and solution we produce

Your responsibilities will be to:

Engage and collaborate with business and technical stakeholders to define requirements and propose solutions that meet business and customer needs and align with business and technology strategy
Lead the design, implementation and testing of technology solutions and report on delivery commitments to ensure solutions are implemented as expected and to agreed timeframes
Establish, build and maintain stakeholder relationships through effective, communication, negotiation and issues management to ensure stakeholders are engaged effectively throughout project ideation and delivery
